hooks.prompt:
Use the `ziki-prime` skill to load the Ziki wiki index for this session. The skill handles everything: reading ~/.claude/ziki.md, fetching wiki/_index.md via the configured vault access method, enforcing size budgets, and handling the no-config and vault-unreachable cases. Do NOT reimplement any of that logic here.

Take the primer block the skill returns and wrap it in this exact JSON shape, then return it as your final output:

{
  "hookSpecificOutput": {
    "hookEventName": "SessionStart",
    "additionalContext": "<primer block from ziki-prime skill, verbatim>"
  }
}

If the skill returns an empty string (Ziki is not configured), return additionalContext as an empty string. Never fail the hook — priming is best-effort infrastructure and must not block session startup.
